{
  "stem": "21626.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he said how he fell in love with my mother and hoped that she wouldn't marry that Karel.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Because he wanted to grow up and marry her.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And how my mother, because she was a marvelous cook, when they were in Hamburg, she was cooking actually for the Germans-- German staff there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And she always managed to sneak some food.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And she was keeping my aunt, and my Aunt Milla, and other people alive by helping them to survive by adding, you know, to their diet; and of course, risking her own life by pinching the food; and things like that.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I started going to school as soon as I arrived.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Luckily, for me, there were two of my classmates from England in the same gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I said luckily, because it was so strange.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I mean, in our school, in Wales, we were treated with kindness, and with compassion, and thoughtfulness.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And here, back in Czechoslovakia, although everybody knew we were orphaned and the way our parents had died, and the rest of our families, they almost resented the fact that we had survived.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you know, they sort of looked upon us as if to say, what are you doing there?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I thought Hitler got you all.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think they were impregnated with this antisemitic doctrine which had been dished out by the Germans during those long years of occupation.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because it did pass after, you know, after a couple of years.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I would say that Czechoslovakia, particularly the Czech parts and the Moravian parts, are the least antisemitic in Europe.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But obviously, there was some-- some there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were also envious of the fact that we spent the war years [LAUGHS] in England, forgetting that we had all the bombing.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
